{"title_page": "List of University of Guelph people", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\nThe following is a list of notable alumni, faculty and affiliates of [[University of Guelph]] in Canada.\n\n==Chancellors==\nAt its first convocation on May 21, 1965 George Drew was installed as chancellor of the University.<ref>{{cite book |title=Fitzhenry and Whiteside Book of Canadian Facts and Dates |last=Pound |first=Richard W. |publisher=Fitzhenry and Whiteside |year=2005}}</ref>\n\n*[[George A. Drew|George Drew]] (1965\u20131971)\n*[[Emmett Matthew Hall]] (1971\u20131977)\n*[[Pauline Mills McGibbon]] (1977\u20131983)\n*[[William Atcheson Stewart]] (1983\u20131989)\n*[[Edmund Bovey]] (1989\u20131990)\n*[[Lincoln Alexander]] (1991\u20132007)\n*[[Pamela Wallin]] (2007\u20132011)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uoguelph.ca/news/2011/03/wallin_resigns.html|title=Wallin Resigns as U of G Chancellor|author=Lori|date=March 31, 2011|publisher=University of Guelph |accessdate=July 5, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[David Mirvish]] (2012\u20132017)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uoguelph.ca/news/2012/02/david_mirvish_n.html|title=David Mirvish Named Eighth U of G Chancellor|author=Lori|date=February 14, 2012|publisher=University of Guelph |accessdate=July 5, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Martha Billes]] (2017\u2013present)<ref name=\"Martha Billes\">{{cite web|url=http://news.uoguelph.ca/2017/04/newchancellor/|title=Martha Billes Named University of Guelph's Ninth Chancellor|publisher=University of Guelph}}</ref>\n\n==Presidents==\n*[[John Douglas MacLachlan]] (1964\u20131967)\n*[[William Winegard]] (1967\u20131975)\n*[[Donald Forster]] (1975\u20131983)\n*[[Burton Matthews]] (1983\u20131988)\n*[[Brian Segal]] (1988\u20131993)\n*[[Mordechai Rozanski]] (1993\u20132003)\n*[[Alastair Summerlee]] (2003\u20132014)\n*[[Franco Vaccarino]] (2014\u20132020)\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Jared \"Toasty\" MacIntyre ]] \u2013 Top tagpro player in the world (https://koalabeast.com/boards)\n*[[Allan Armitage]] \u2013 author and professor at the [[University of Georgia]]<ref>[https://www.timberpress.com/author/237 Profile: Allan M. Armitage] Timber Press</ref>\n*[[Rupan Bal]] \u2013 Canadian\u2013Indian YouTuber<ref name=\"thestar.com\">[https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2014/05/15/from_youtube_sensations_to_punjabi_movie_stars.html \"From YouTube sensations to Punjabi movie stars\"]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', May 15, 2014.</ref>\n*[[Chris Banks (poet)|Chris Banks]] \u2013 poet<ref>[https://litlive.blogspot.com/2011/01/chris-banks.html?m=1 Profile:Chris Banks]</ref>\n*[[Toby Barrett]] \u2013 politician, [[Member of Provincial Parliament (Ontario)|Member of Provincial Parliament]] for [[Haldimand\u2014Norfolk]]<ref>[https://tobybarrett.com/ Toby Barrett: MPP Haldimand Norfolk] tobybarrett.com</ref>\n*[[Karen Beauchemin]] \u2013 research scientist<ref>[https://www.asas.org/taking-stock/blog-post/taking-stock/2011/09/14/meet-a-speaker-dr-karen-beauchemin Meet a speaker: Dr. Karen Beauchemin] ASAS</ref>\n*[[Deni Ellis B\u00e9chard]] \u2013 [[Canadian-American]] novelist<ref>[https://www.misericordia.edu/page.cfm?p=500&newsid=2734 Noted author Deni B\u00e9chard offering readings from new novel, 'Into the Sun'] Misericordia University</ref>\n*[[Jennifer Beech]]\n*[[Laura Bertram]] \u2013 actress<ref name=\"uoguelph\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uoguelph.ca/atguelph/06-09-13/profile.shtml|title=A Good Move|accessdate=August 11, 2007|author=Rebecca Kendall|date=September 13, 2006|publisher=University of Guelph}}</ref>\n*[[Mark Bourrie]] \u2013 lawyer and journalist\n*[[Tim Bray]] \u2013 [[software developer]] and entrepreneur\n* [[Sara Angelucci]] \u2013 artist and professor at [[Ryerson University]]<ref>[https://www.imagearts.ryerson.ca/?page_id=261 FACULTY School of Image Arts] Ryerson University</ref>\n*[[Harry Brightwell]]\n*[[Ryder Britton]]\n*[[Christa Brosseau]]\n*[[James Robert Brown]]\n*[[Krista Buecking]]\n*[[Kathy Butler]]\n*[[Cassie Campbell]]\n*[[Dom Cardillo]]\n*[[David Castle (philosopher)|David Castle]]\n*[[Anna Chatterton]]\n*[[Laurel Schafer]], [[Canada Research Chair]] in Catalyst Development\n*[[Dicki Chhoyang]]\n*[[George Chiang]]\n*[[Meredith Chivers]]\n*[[Olivia Chow]]\n*[[Reid Coolsaet]]\n*[[Claude Cormier]]\n*[[Anne Croy]], Reproductive immunologist \n*[[Elisabeth de Mariaffi]]\n*[[Diane Deans]]\n*[[Susan Dobson]]\n*[[Peter Donaldson (actor)|Peter Donaldson]]\n*[[Rick Ferraro]]\n*[[Graham Forsythe]]\n*[[James E. Fraser (historian)|James E. Fraser]]\n*[[Nora Gould]]\n*[[Tim Grant (general)|Tim Grant]]\n*[[Peter S. Gray]]\n*[[Tara Hedican]]\n*[[Graham Henderson (lawyer)|Graham Henderson]] \n*[[Stephen Hicks]]\n*[[Robert Horner]]\n*[[Alexis Jordan (swimmer)|Alexis Jordan]]\n*[[David Joseph (basketball)|David Joseph]]\n*[[Mark Lautens]]\n*[[Robert Leigh]]\n*[[Matt Lennox]]\n*[[Canisia Lubrin]]\n*[[Karen Ludwig]]\n*[[Judy Maddren]]\n*[[Brandon Maxwell (ice hockey)|Brandon Maxwell]]\n*[[Tom McBroom]]\n*[[Scott McGillivray]]\n*[[Audrey McLaughlin]]\n*[[Heather McNairn]]\n*[[Gord Miller (environmental commissioner)|Gord Miller]]\n*[[K. D. Miller]]\n*[[Kenneth Mitchell (actor)|Kenneth Mitchell]]\n*[[Kimberly Moffit]]\n*[[Peter Moss]]\n*[[Jacey Murphy]]\n*[[Ian Murray (Canadian politician)|Ian Murray]]\n*[[Brendan Myers]]\n*[[Opendra Narayan]]\n*[[Piers Nash]]\n*[[Joe Neilands]]\n*[[Penny Park]]\n*[[Kim Parlee]]\n*[[Roula Partheniou]] \u2013 artist\n*[[Cecil Frederick Patterson]]\n*[[David Peck]]\n*[[Mirela Rahneva]]\n*[[Lisa Raitt]]\n*[[Jordan Raycroft]]\n*[[Sue Richards (artist)|Sue Richards]]\n*[[Jael Richardson]]\n*[[Jack Roxburgh]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Roxy dies from injuries (continued from page 1)|date=February 28, 1975|newspaper=Simcoe Reformer|location=Simcoe, Ontario|page=12}}</ref>\n*[[Doug Rollins]]\n*[[Liz Sandals]]\n*[[Dolph Schluter]]\n*[[James Schroder]]\n*[[H. B. Sharman]]\n*[[Kalidas Shetty]]\n*[[Vandana Shiva]]\n*[[Jane Siberry]]\n*[[Ralph Spence (bishop)|Ralph Spence]]\n*[[John Steffler]]\n*[[Derek Sullivan (